The paper investigates the goal-setting and achievement process in activity tracking apps, which is a core feature of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study focuses on weight loss goals in MyFitnessPal, which involves analyzing user behavior and attitudes towards achieving their goals, making it relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to analyze user comments, which falls under computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
